    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In bookbinding, the process of sawing grooves in the back of a text block for the reception of cords on which the gatherings are sewn.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
